   WHAT EVERY EXECUTIVE NEEDS TO KNOW ABOUT GLOBAL WARMING
</P>
<P>
   GLOBAL-WARMING-HARVARD-BUSINESS-REVIEW _ In December 1997,
global warming began to assume a prominent position on business
executives' agendas. That's when representatives of 160 nations,
convened by the United Nations in Kyoto, Japan, adopted a plan that
would limit the amounts of greenhouse gases being released into the
atmosphere. If ratified, the Kyoto Protocol will require industrial
nations to dramatically reduce emissions of those gases by 2012.
Here, a look at how shifts in the weather and potential regulatory
changes will impact businesses. 1,400 words. By Kimberly O'Neill
Packard and Forest Reinhardt.
