<P>
   YOUTH-VOTE (Washington) _ In a sweeping effort to energize 18-
to-21-year-old voters, national youth and civic groups are
organizing mock elections and debates moderated by young adults.
These groups are mounting a massive campaign, alarmed by a trend
that shows young people are increasingly steering clear of the
voting booth. By JUDY HOLLAND.
