<HEADLINE>
TOUCHED BY ANGELS 
</HEADLINE>
  ATTENTION EDITORS: The following material from The New York Times
Syndicate is for use by clients of ``HIGH STYLE AND MORE.''
Nonsubscribers can use this article only by special arrangement.
For purchase information, see end of text. 
 (Three color slides are available.) 
 From WWD 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
 &HT;    
 &HT;    Roll back the clock.
 &HT;    After a decade of sleek, silvery minimalism, juniors are looking
with fondness at late '70s-early '80s wear, with a special fondness
for anything ultra-sexy or anything ``Charlie's Angels.''
 &HT;    Color is still big news, but preferred hues are going more
earthy, deepening away from sunny turquoise and fuchsia into burnt
orange, rust, olives, wines and cognacs. And purple: Junior
manufacturers said they're planning a royal push of the color.
 &HT;    Here, a look.
 &HT;    
