<P>
   SHARP-DRIVING _ ATLANTA _ Unless you have been under a rock or
on a deserted tropical island, you have heard of Firestone's tire
recall. Hopefully, regardless of what brand of tire your vehicle
wears, you have heeded warnings to maintain the proper air
pressure. Traveling across many Southern states this summer, I have
noticed a marked increase in the population of interstate
alligators _ you know, those carcasses of big truck tires in the
middle of the road. I blame the increase on one thing: heat.
(Sharp, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   THE-MECHANIC _ ATLANTA _ A natural extension of my job as an
automotive service technology instructor is to match the student to
a position that will provide an advantageous union between the
student and the employer. Considering the shortage of qualified
auto mechanics, this might seem an easy task. I find it just the
opposite. Our office receives several phone calls a week with pleas
from prospective employers to send them students. Unfortunately,
many of them have unreal expectations of the skills and recourses
(primarily tools) an automotive tech student possesses. (Carter,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
