<P>
   OPPORTUNISTS _ It has been such a long time since Christopher
Walken has played anything close to a mentally balanced character,
that we watch and wait now for the expected signs of psychosis
whenever he is on screen. In the gritty working-class Queens drama
The Opportunists, he isn't creepy or crazy, just a decent guy named
Vic Kelly, who tries to escape his criminal past and fails
miserably at it. This is a satisfying change of pace for Walken,
given the opportunity to flex different acting muscles, but his
vehicle sputters and lurches just like the cars Kelly tries unsu
DRIVER STANDINGS BUSCH SERIES
