<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FILM-THECREW-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
A COMEDY WITH TEETH, EVEN IF THEY ARE FALSE
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
 By TODD CAMP 
 c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   As Richard Dreyfuss' unmistakable nasal voice comes up over the
first reel of this surprisingly charming little comedy, you'll
probably feel flashback pains for ``Stand By Me.''
</P>
<P>
   The similarities might be coincidental, but probably not. After
all, this is also a story of four friends whose lives were
intertwined as youth. But unlike the naive youngsters of the Rob
Reiner film, the young wiseguys in ``The Crew'' have seen more than
their share of corpses.
</P>
<P>
   What they didn't see coming is that after years of putting out
hits and making people offers they couldn't refuse, they'd wind up
a quartet of elderly has-beens knocking about sunny Miami Beach.
</P>
<P>
   Dreyfuss' Bobby Bartellemeo is the brains of the outfit, with
Joey ``Bats'' Pistella (Burt Reynolds) as the hothead, Mike ``The
Brick'' Donatelli (Dan Hedaya) as the feeb and Tony ``Mouth''
Donato (Seymour Cassel) as the strong, silent type.
</P>
<P>
   Stuck in a ramshackle hotel that is being renovated and sold off
to a wealthier, younger clientele, the geriatric goombahs concoct a
scheme to keep from losing their turf. They swipe a corpse from the
morgue and fake a Mafia-style hit in the lobby. Trouble is, the
stiff turns out to the long-lost papa of a well-connected local
drug lord, prompting a gangland war that continues to spiral out of
control.
</P>
<P>
   Dreyfuss lays on the accent a little thick, but all four of the
Grumpy Old GoodFellas pull off likable performances, especially
Hedaya. Good supporting work comes from Jennifer Tilly as a working
girl who gets wind of their scheme, Jeremy Piven as a detective on
the case, Lainie Kazan as Tilly's restaurant maven stepmom and
Miguel Sandoval as the terminally confused drug lord. It's a comedy
with some teeth, even if they are false.
</P>
<P>
   (Todd Camp is a film critic for the Star-Telegram. Visit the
Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
