   MEXICO-U.S. (Washington) _ Vicente Fox, the man who will be
president of Mexico, met Thursday with Bill Clinton and Al Gore,
and envisioned a Mexico far closer to the United States, on a
continent where borders are only lines on a map. Fox, who will take
office Dec. 1, came to the United States to meet the man who will
be its next president: After an hour with Gore, he is to meet Gov.
George W. Bush in Texas on Friday. By Tim Weiner.
