Communications and the last of its 86,000 of its employees, but for
thousands of customers on the East Coast, the effect of the walkout
lives on. It will take about a month to work through about 50,000
delayed repairs and more than 200,000 orders for new service as a
result of the strike which lasted 15 days in New York and New
England and 18 days in several mid-Atlantic states. By Simon
Romero.
