   SCI-LIFE-ORIGINS (Undated) _ A maverick theory about the origin
of life has received striking support from an experiment designed
to mimic the violent interactions of rock and common gases that
would occur under the Hadean conditions of extreme heat and
pressure that would have occurred on or underneath the early earth
or its oceans. The experiment, scientists are reporting Thursday,
succeeded in synthesizing a rare molecule crucial to metabolism in
all forms of life. By Nicholas Wade.
