<HEADLINE>
CARTOONS GET HIP IN KIDS' WB SERIES `GENERATION O!'
</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  By LANA BERKOWITZ 
c. 2000 Houston Chronicle 
Can't miss Molly O's big mouth. She makes a living with it, and
sometimes it gets her into kid-size trouble.
<TEXT>
<P>
   In the new Kids' WB animated Saturday morning series
``Generation O!,'' Molly O is a singer for a top rock band, and
she's only 8 years old.
</P>
<P>
   She's rich and famous, but she still lives at home with her
loving, but clueless, parents. There's also an older brother, Buzz,
who Molly O says can be ``very, very annoying.''
</P>
<P>
   Her bandmates are quirky, too: Cousin Eddie (Edwina) plays lead
guitar, Nub is the bass player, and the drummer is a kangaroo named
Yo-Yo.
</P>
<P>
   The series opens on a topical note in this election year with a
political episode. It's titled ``Damp Sheets.'' Ask a member of the
target audience, ages 6-11, what that means, and see if you get a
giggle.
</P>
<P>
   During this election story, Molly O flies to Washington, D.C.,
to sing her song ``Favorite Son'' in support of a senator's
presidential campaign. Along the way she discovers the senator is
not a nice man. He mistreats his dog, Rayburn, even pulls the poor
hound's ears, a la Lyndon Johnson.
</P>
<P>
   Molly O balks at supporting the politician, but the unscrupulous
senator threatens to reveal one of Molly O's embarrassing secrets
if she doesn't perform. Yes, her secret is a bed-wetting accident
after an overindulgence of juice.
</P>
<P>
   After much agonizing, she performs. But she slips in her new
song ``Damp Sheets.'' It's not a rousing Bruce Springsteen rocker,
but it gets the crowd on its feet.
</P>
<P>
   The original songs in the 13 half-hour episodes are written and
performed by Letters to Cleo, a Boston-based band that appeared in
the film ``10 Things I Hate About You.'' Lead singer Kay Hanley has
recorded five songs for the upcoming live-action film ``Josie and
the Pussycats.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Generation O!'' offers positive messages about friendship and
responsibility in a cheery package. And there's no violence, unless
you count the sister-brother tussles.
</P>
<P>
   The Saturday morning debut continues Kids' WB's rollout of new
series. ``Generation O!'' will settle into a Friday afternoon time
slot when the Saturday morning lineup debuts Sept. 23.
</P>
<P>
   X X X END OF STORY
</P>
<P>
   $$$
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
