</P>
<P>
   Abruzzese said that Burnett helped sell the show to the list of
nine sponsors who signed on before it began, including Reebok
shoes, Budweiser Beer, Target stores and Ericsson phones. ``They
got one of the best deals ever, tremendous bang for their buck,''
Moonves said.
</P>
<P>
   But once the show became a hit, CBS began selling an additional
minute of advertising in the show each week, mainly to movie
companies. CBS extended the finale from one hour to two hours and
had the whole second hour to sell at new prices, which reached as
high as $600,000 for a 30-second commercial. The network also sold
the hourlong discussion show that followed at lower rates.
</P>
<P>
   Burnett shared in all that new advertising revenue. ``He got
half and we got half,'' Abruzzese said.
</P>
<P>
   ``Mark Burnett is definitely becoming a very wealthy man,''
Moonves said.  &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-08-24-00 2007EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
