underneath Manhattan when a thin, animated man named Ralph had an
idea. ``Someone should be making a film about this stuff,'' he
said. Marc Singer still finds it hard to believe that an idle
remark inspired such an odyssey that led a 20-year-old who had
never picked up a camera to live underground himself, enlist his
fellow outcasts as his crew and put together ``Dark Days,'' a
documentary that won three awards at this year's Sundance Film
Festival. Singer in a Manhattan subway station recently. (Nicole
