<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    u B5E11946EDS: Embargoed for Sunday.
 &HT;    Classic lines meet modern attitudes
 &HT;    By Meredith Moss
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAYTON, Ohio _
</P>
<P>
   ``While the philosophy of etiquette must be everlasting, the
practice of manners is ever changing. Times have changed
dramatically and with them, the kinds of things we need to know to
practice impeccable manners have changed, as well.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Peggy Post
</P>
<P>
   For some, fashion's nod to the past is nostalgic. It reminds us
of favorite outfits we _ or our mothers and grandmothers _ wore
long ago.
</P>
<P>
   For younger folks attracted to old Hollywood films and vintage
shops, it's a chance to get into the act. This passion for
``dressing up'' is fun _ with an emphasis on elegance, shine and
glamour.
</P>
<P>
   There are influences from many decades _ beat looks from the
'50s, hippie psychedelic prints and bellbottoms from the '60s.
</P>
<P>
   But no era is more important this season than the 1940s _ with
its tweed and herringbone fitted suits, soft, feminine blouses and
glamorous furs. The newest shoes have a vintage feel _ open toes,
wedge heels, ankle-strap or T-strap shapes.
</P>
<P>
   What better place than Carillon Historical Park to combine
beautiful objects from the 1940s with contemporary fashion takes on
those special years?
</P>
<P>
   PHOTO 1: COUPLE ON TRAIN.
</P>
<P>
   ``A lady invariably precedes her escort down the aisle of the
train and takes the inside seat....women should dress quietly and
inconspicuously when traveling.''
</P>
<P>
   _ From Book of Etiquette, 1923.
</P>
<P>
   BOARDING TIME: On her: natural Russian sable coat ($55,000),
shell ($250) and cardigan ($360), from TSE; cream skirt ($305) from
Les Copains, gold beaded necklace ($320), burgundy Mary Jane strap
shoe ($188) from DKNY. On him: blue pinstripe suit ($2,075) from
Ermenegildo Zegna; shirt ($220) from Ermenegildo Zegna, blue tie
($79.50), black shoes ($350) from Ferragamo and pocket square
($25). Photographed on a 1903 Barney &AMP; Smith parlor car at Carillon
Historical Park in Dayton.
</P>
<P>
   PHOTO 2: THREESOME WALKING ARM-IN-ARM, MAN WEARING HAT: ``While
lifting the hat one should incline the head and slightly smile. But
it must be remembered that the unmannerly habit of touching the
hat, instead of lifting it is an indication of sheer laziness and a
lack of gallantry.'' _ From Book of Etiquette, 1923.
</P>
<P>
   SUITABLY SPEAKING: (left to right) Turquoise sleeveless dress
($295) and blazer ($430) from Michael Kors; gray pearl necklace
($320), opalescent pearl necklace ($457), earrings ($110) and black
handbag ($340) from Miu Miu. Fedora ($71.90) from Phillip Treacy;
gray windowpane suit ($1,595) from Armani; shirt ($215) and red tie
($120) from Ermenegildo Zegna; pocket square ($25). Red jacket
($585) and skirt ($280) from Les Copains; black necklace ($175)
from St. John; leopard print hat ($250) from Phillip Treacy.
</P>
<P>
   PHOTO 3: COUPLE ON OLD BIKES, TALKING
</P>
<P>
   ``In talking to a stranger who has just been introduced to you
and about whom you are in complete ignorance, there is really
nothing to do but try one topic after another just as a fisherman
searches for the right fly.'' _ From Etiquette by Emily Post, 1945.
</P>
<P>
   WELL-SPOKEN: His leather jacket ($550) and pants ($85) from
Ralph Lauren, brown suede shoe ($165) from Cole Haan. Her cardigan
($545) and brown pants ($395) from TSE, green plaid scarf ($68)
from Echo and shoes ($150) from Donald Pliner. Nostalgic Huffy
bikes from the collection at Carillon Historical Park.
</P>
<P>
   PHOTO 4: GLAMOUR SHOT ON STEPS WITH FUR....
</P>
<P>
   ``The woman who is chic is always a little different. She adapts
the fashion to her own personality.''
</P>
<P>
   _ From Emily Post's Etiquette, 1945.
</P>
<P>
   GLAMOUR IN STEP: Black fox cashmere cape ($1,995), black velvet
jacket ($1,295) and pants ($795) from Armani, black necklace ($175)
and bracelet ($155) from St. John, black evening handbag ($95) and
black shoe ($310) from Calvin Klein.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
