<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FALLSTYLE-MUSTHAVES0827-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    u B5E11946EDS: Embargoed for Sunday.
 &HT;    Size up the season's essentials
 &HT;    By Meredith Moss
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAYTON, Ohio _ Not many of us can afford to purchase a new
wardrobe every season.
</P>
<P>
   Fortunately, it's not necessary. A few key items will have you
looking fashionable for fall.
</P>
<P>
   _ Women who have missed wearing blouses will be delighted to
know they're back. Perfect this season is a silk blouse with a
matching or attached self-tie scarf. You'll see ultra feminine
versions with ruffles at the neck.
</P>
<P>
   _ Leather is hotter than ever. Consider a classic black leather
skirt or blazer. The newest take is embossed leathers, especially
in python, crocodile or cobra patterns. There are patchwork
patterns in leather, suede, fur and denim.
</P>
<P>
   _ A great matched suit is a staple. Pair a waist- or hip-length
fitted jacket with matching pant (most have a flat front) or
simple-line skirt. A fashion-forward length is either just below
the knee or well below the knee, but not ankle length. Fabrics
include tweeds and wool boucles. Consider a fitted suit with fur
collar that recalls the 1940s; pair it with a coordinated blouse.
Look for accents of leather, cashmere and for seam details. Jackets
are often belted, and pants are fitted and slender but some have a
fuller leg.
</P>
<P>
   _ Luxurious fabrics abound: cashmere, silks and satins, feathers
and fur. Pashmina is still with us; this year's version adds
embellishment. A key item is a textured, chunky, colorful sweater
in a cashmere or cashmere blend.
</P>
<P>
   _ A great coat can not only protect you from the elements but
ensure a feminine and sophisticated look as well. Fabrics range
from luxurious to high-tech, and many repel water. Check out a
fitted, back-belted coat, a leather trench or a black-and-white
herringbone tweed. The newest coat length is to the knee.
</P>
<P>
   _ Lauren is just one of the designers highlighting tartan plaids
this season. Look for pleated skirts or kilts, matching scarves,
plaid coats, tartan plaid bags for girls. It's also the season for
an Argyle sweater.
</P>
<P>
   _ Fur can be faux or real; you'll see it everywhere _ as collar
or cuff trim on suits or jackets and coats.
</P>
<P>
   _ Fashion continues its love affair with color. Although fall
neutrals (black, gray, tan) are always a staple, this season you'll
also see strong colors with names such as raspberry, loden, paprika
and grenadine. Combine an intensely bright jacket with black or
dark brown pants or try color blocking _ combining bright hues.
Don't be afraid of turquoise, chartreuse, shocking pink or purple.
</P>
<P>
   _ Now that we've been introduced to the new stretch fabric
blends, we'll never give them up. Consider a pair of cropped
stretch pants, stretch angoras and wools, denim-and-stretch jeans,
a stretch charmeuse bow blouse.
</P>
<P>
   A great accessory can give an outfit an entirely new look. Keep
an eye out for these:
</P>
<P>
   _ Gold jewelry. It's no surprise that the return to ladylike
fashion means trading silver for gold. It needn't be the real
thing, of course, but a gold watch, lariat necklace, cuff or bangle
bracelet will add class to any outfit. One essential: the hoop
earring. Mesh metals also abound. And it's the perfect time to get
out your mother's pearls.
</P>
<P>
   _ A knee-high boot with a pointed toe and sculpted heel. You'll
find it in stretch leather for a great silhouette. Retro pumps are
feminine and tailored, definitely designed for comfort. Look for
T-straps, slingbacks, ankle straps and open toes.
</P>
<P>
   _ Animal prints are back again, for blouses and jackets,
handbags and shoes. New looks include python and ostrich, but
leopard, pony and zebra still are popular.
</P>
<P>
   _ Bags, especially fabric bags, continue to be important. Look
for clutch, baguette, chain strap and doctor's bag or bowling bag
shapes. The Coach collection, for example, ranges from Woolrich
blanket totes and Bleecker wools to dark denims and pony hair in
black, deep red, orange and vicuna. Look for little faux fur
handbags, totes in every size, soft leathers and suede hobos.
You'll also spot bags in patent-leather colors, plaids, tweeds and
metallics.
</P>
<P>
   _ Opaques are back, not that those of us who battle Midwestern
winters ever considered giving them away. Mix this season's bold
colors with black tights. You'll also find tights in colors,
textures and patterns.
</P>
<P>
   _ Skinny belts can be worn with pants, over suit jackets and
knit dresses; there are chain belts, animal skins and rhinestone
looks.
</P>
<P>
   _ Check out the aviator look in sunglasses. Rimless glasses are
popular as well; watch for geometrics.
</P>
<P>
   _ Scarves come in every size and pattern; they're the perfect
match for a polished look.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
