<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    u B5E11946EDS: Embargoed for Sunday.
 &HT;    Social graces: It's time to be a lady again
 &HT;    By Meredith Moss
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAYTON, Ohio _ You're invited to someone's home for dinner or a
party and have no idea what to wear.
</P>
<P>
   Think about ``dressing like a lady'' and you'll be on the right
fashion track.
</P>
<P>
   Women won't go wrong this season if they pair a pretty sweater
in a yummy color with a suede or leather skirt or pants.
</P>
<P>
   ``Women are excited to see a ladylike, feminine edge move back
into fashion this fall,'' says Paula Daedelow, regional
special-events coordinator for Lazarus. ``I think women are ready
for this fashion movement because they love to dress up.''
</P>
<P>
   If you love red, this is your year. From crimson to cherry,
you'll see it on clothing as well as accessories, with the darker
hues being the most important for fall. If head-to-toe red is too
bright for your taste, try using it as an accent. Pair a red
sweater with dark pants or slip a red blouse under a traditional
suit.
</P>
<P>
   If it's a dressier evening, consider the always-acceptable
little black dress or a feminine blouse and dressy skirt.
</P>
<P>
   Accessories can add flair to any outfit: a pashmina wrap, a slim
python belt or slinky open-toed shoe, some gold bangles.
</P>
<P>
   Men might layer a good-looking polo or V-neck sweater in
cashmere or silk and cotton knit with a T-shirt, then pair it with
a khaki or dress slacks.
</P>
<P>
   PHOTO 1: COUPLE BRINGS FLOWERS
</P>
<P>
   ``Flowers make the best gift for a dinner hostess.''
</P>
<P>
   _ From Emily Post's Etiquette by Peggy Post
</P>
<P>
   POSY PRESENT: Sueded python print wrap coat from Marvin Richards
($240), charcoal gray sweater jacket ($135), chevron shirt
($52.50), black pants ($125), all from Cezani. Both outfits from
Parisian.
</P>
<P>
   PHOTO 2: OPENING GIFT
</P>
<P>
   ``You should open gifts when they are given, except for wedding
gifts or gifts at a large party where opening many gifts would be
impossible. ``
</P>
<P>
   _ From Etiquette for Dummies by Sue Fox
</P>
<P>
   SOFT WRAP: Plaid boucle sweater wrap ($198), textured mock-neck
berry sweater ($158) and dark sand side-zip pants ($118), all from
Sigrid Olsen. Merlot V-neck sweater ($70), plaid shirt ($52.50) and
black pants ($125), all from Cezani. Both outfits from Parisian.
</P>
<P>
   PHOTO 3: LINGERIE SHOT
</P>
<P>
   ``A quick note sent to thank someone for a favor, a party or a
present is a simple way to let a person know that you appreciate
the efforts expended.''
</P>
<P>
   _ From Emily Post's Etiquette by Peggy Post
</P>
<P>
   AT-HOME ELEGANCE: White applique dressing gown ($170) and robe
($135) from Flora Nikarooz. From Saks Fifth Avenue, Cincinnati.
