<SLUG> BC-TV-WEEKEND25-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    TV week highlights
 &HT;    By Phil Kloer
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Tonight
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  f+b``Big Brother'' f-b(8 on CBS, 1361, and 8 p.m. Saturday,
7317) _ Day Two of ``Survivor'' withdrawal dawns, and it seems an
appropriate time to turn the whirring, wall-mounted camera back to
CBS' other reality series, ``Big Brother.''
</P>
<P>
   And oh, brother. After the finale fireworks of ``Survivor''
Wednesday, going back into that sad little house feels more like
Chinese water torture than ever.
</P>
<P>
   ``Big Brother'' is still watchable, in a ghastly,
peek-through-your-fingers sort of way, and still better than summer
reruns.
</P>
<P>
   But a little past the halfway point in CBS' 100-day experiment
in sensory deprivation, it's hard to tell who's more lethargic _
the seven remaining house-hostages or the viewing audience.
</P>
<P>
   It's partly the audience's fault, for voting out the only three
people who really stirred things up _ black activist Will ``Mega''
Collins, stripper-provocateur Jean Jordan and Froot Loopy Hoosier
homemaker Karen Fowler. Most of the remaining guinea pigs are too
nice to make waves; this is what happens when Rodney King's wish _
``Can't we all just get along?''_ comes to pass.
</P>
<P>
   The producers have been trying to spice things up, giving them a
puppy (even though they already have Brittany Petros) and sneaking
Will back into and out of the house earlier this week (although by
sneaking him, they missed the chance for a major moment).
</P>
<P>
   Don't be surprised if CBS starts amping up ``Big Brother'' to
try to build a buzz. Hint: You can't go wrong with forcing people
to eat live beetle larvae.
</P>
<P>
   Saturday
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  f+b``Miss Teen USA Pageant'' f-b(9 p.m. on CBS, 4684) _ Just
how prestigious is this particular pageant? It's live from
Shreveport, La.
</P>
<P>
   Sunday
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  f+b``Daria: Is It Fall Yet?''f-b (7 p.m. on MTV, 487911) _ Dry
as an Atlanta back yard, Daria is MTV's coolest cartoon character.
Sunday night, she gets her first movie, in which she is forced to
volunteer at a summer camp for the oversensitive called the OK to
Cry Corral.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  f+b``The Simpsons'' f-b(8 p.m. on Fox, 3337) _ If PBS pledge
breaks make you break out in boils, take a gander at what happens
when they get Simpson-ized in this classic rerun.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  f+b``Witchblade'' f-b(8 p.m. on TNT, 908089) _ Yancyf+tCQf-t
Butler (that's right, Yancy, not Nancy) stars in this new sci-fi
flick based on a comic book. She plays a New York City cop who
discovers a magical bracelet that gives her supernatural powers and
won't even turn her wrist green.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  f+b``The E! True Hollywood Story: All in the Family.'' f-b(9
p.m. on E!, 175824) _ As much a part of TV's pantheon as ``All in
the Family'' deserves to be, it would be almost impossible to get
it on a major network today. Not that it was easy in 1971. Carroll
O'Connor, Rob Reiner and Jean Stapleton reminisce about when those
were the days.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  f+b``The Chieftains Over Ireland'' f-b(10 p.m. on A&AMP;E, 828398)
_ The Irish band performs in Ireland. Irish music, no doubt.
</P>
<P>
   Movies
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  f+b``Pee-wee's Big Adventure'' f-b(10:15 a.m. Saturday on
Showtime, 47077775) _ Not the one in the Sarasota theater, the one
where his bike is stolen.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  f+b``High Noon'' f-b(10 p.m. Saturday on Turner Classic
Movies, 1604881) _ Not last week's remake with Tom Skerritt but the
original, with Gary Cooper and Grace Kelly.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  f+b``Rob Roy'' f-b(8 p.m. Sunday on NBC, 565176) _ Not the
mixed drink, but the Scottish outlaw, played here by Liam Neeson.
</P>
