<P>
   MOVIES-BRINGITON _ Movie Review: ``Bring It On.'' Comedy with
cheerleaders at competition. Grade: C-. (BLongino, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-THECREW _ Movie review: ``The Crew.'' Old geezers revive
the mob. Grade: F. (StMurray, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 13.
</P>
<P>
   CREW-WISEGUYS _ Move over, Space Cowboys, there's a new quartet
of senior wise guys in town. Literally ``wise guys'' in this case,
for the foursome of Michael Dinner's The Crew are aged lower
echelon New Jersey mobsters. Now reduced to sitting out their
sunset days on the porch of their South Beach old age home, they
reminisce as they watch the suddenly trendy area get yuppified
around them. (Erstein, Palm Beach Post). 25.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-THEEDGE _ Movie review: ``The Edge,'' skateboarding flick
playing weekends in Kennesaw megaplex. Grade: B-. (BLongino,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 10.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-TIMEREGAINED _ Movie review: ``Time Regained.'' Long
French film. (Ringel, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-OPPORTUNISTS _ It has been such a long time since
Christopher Walken has played anything close to a mentally balanced
character, that we watch and wait now for the expected signs of
psychosis whenever he is on screen. In the gritty working-class
Queens drama The Opportunists, he isn't creepy or crazy, just a
decent guy named Vic Kelly, who tries to escape his criminal past
and fails miserably at it. This is a satisfying change of pace for
Walken, given the opportunity to flex different acting muscles, but
his vehicle sputters and lurches just like the cars Kelly tries
unsuccessfully to repair. (Erstein, Palm beach Post). 25.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-TAO-STEVE _ PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Listen closely and feel
free to take notes at ``The Tao of Steve,'' in which a pudgy,
philosophy-spouting, pot smoker reveals his secrets for becoming a
chick magnet. Who says movies can't be entertaining and
educational? (Erstein, Palm beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-MINIREVIEWS _ Mini reviews of all currently playing
movies. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
