<SLUG> BC-MOBY-BOUGHT-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
OREGON FIRM NETS MOBY DISC MUSIC STORES
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By PAM PARK 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Moby Disc, a store that sells used and new music,
has been swallowed by an Oregon online music retailer.
</P>
<P>
   The addition of Moby Disc's six Los Angeles-area locations will
bring Portland-based Djangos.com's family of stores to 19.
</P>
<P>
   Djangos' vision is to combine the best used-music retailers in
major metropolitan markets into one family and overlay that with
online technology, said Steve Wood, chairman and CEO of Djangos.
</P>
<P>
   Moby Disc's name will not change, nor will much else. Djangos
acquires unique stores with a good reputation and loyal customers.
Since it's not broken, Djangos won't try to fix it, Wood said.
</P>
<P>
   ``What Djangos is about is taking the best used products and the
most unique stores available to you as a music enthusiast,'' Wood
said.
</P>
<P>
   The added benefit for customers will be Djangos' ability to make
more titles available. The acquisition of Moby Disc adds 70,000
units to the Djangos 1million-unit inventory.
</P>
<P>
   If a desired title is not available in the local Moby Disc
store, customers will soon be able to use Internet-connected
in-store kiosks to find that particular piece of music or format in
other Djangos stores. The music can be shipped to the customer.
</P>
<P>
   Music can also be ordered from home through the Djangos Web
site.
</P>
<P>
   ``It allows us to manage a global inventory,'' Wood said.
</P>
<P>
   Djangos owns stores in Chicago, Portland and Seattle. The Moby
Disc acquisition is the company's entrance into the Los Angeles
market and is its largest acquisition to date. Djangos plans
another acquisition by year-end, Wood said, but he declined to name
the stores or locations.
</P>
<P>
   Moby Disc was founded in 1972 by Mark Ferjulian and Bob Say. The
company has stores in Canoga Park, Sherman Oaks, Pasadena, Santa
Monica, Huntington Beach and Costa Mesa.
</P>
<P>
   In connection with the acquisition, Djangos has named Ferjulian
vice president and Say general manager of Southern California
operations.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's the right opportunity at the right time to move our
stores into the new century,'' Say said. ``It's an opportunity to
get hooked up with the Internet and still do what we do best.''
</P>
<P>
   Djangos is also working with MP3.com to provide streaming
digital versions of music purchases available through an ``instant
listening'' account on the Internet. The instant listening project
is set to get under way this fall, when MP3 finalizes its
agreements with the last of the Big Five record companies.
</P>
<P>
   Customers would then be able to take their favorite music with
them anywhere in the world, without having to carry it, Wood said.
</P>
</TEXT>
